article.headline: Longwood 83, William &amp, Mary 81
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- Martiz Washington had 20 points and six assists and Longwood overcame a 12-point first-half deficit to defeat William & Mary 83-81 on Wednesday night. Washington was 5 of 9 from beyond the arc and the Lancers hit 11 of 24 3-pointers to beat the Tribe for the first time in four tries since 2004. Trailing 40-28 with 1:56 left in the first half, Longwood (5-11) closed to 42-36 at the break. The Lancers took a brief lead at 53-52 on a Durann Neil 3-pointer with 14:52 left, but the Tribe (4-8) quickly regained the advantage. With the score tied at 70, Longwood went on a 9-2 run. William & Mary got within a point on a Brandon Britt 3-pointer with 1 second left, then Jeremiah Bowman sealed the win with a free throw. Bowman finished with 18 points, Antwan Carter had 17 and Aaron Mitchell 12 for the Lancers. Quinn McDowell scored a career-high 30 for the Tribe.
